-- Swiss Re shares up 6 pct on stake bid talk - traders
-- 
-- Wed Mar 12, 2014 04:34AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, March 12 (Reuters) - Shares in Swiss Re <SRENH.VX> rose 6 percent to lead European risers on Wednesday as traders cited talk a trust controlled by Italy's Agnelli family could look to buy a stake in the reinsurer.

Swiss Re declined to comment when contacted by Reuters. Exor, the holding company of the Agnelli family, was not immediately available for comment when contacted by Reuters.